OperationTemplate.description: The operation gets the Geolus object ID. The Geolus is the engine of shape search. The Geolus object ID is used to perform shape search. And the Geolus object id can be used check whether the object is indexed to Geolus. If the object does not be indexed to Geolus, the result will be empty. Use Cases: The operation provides following user case. Use Case 1: You can check whether the Teamcenter object is indexed to Geolus. Use Case 2: The Geolus object ID can be used to perform shape search.
OperationTemplate.name: SS1::Soa::ShapeSearch::ShapeSearch::getGeolusID
OperationTemplate.returnDescription: The Geolus object ID. The following partial errors may be returned: 117002: The specified Teamcenter object UID is empty. 117003: Failed to retrieve the Geolus object ID.

OperationTemplate.description: This operation finds the number of profiles served and display value of each profile in a choice of languages. The operation takes the specific language and sends a request to server to get the display value for profiles and the default profile of server. The profile value uses the default language if the server doesn't know the locale or the locale is empty. Use Cases: The operation provides following user case. Use Case 1: You can find the profiles and their order provided by the server. Use Case 2: Query default profile used for searches on web pages or from plugin clients.
OperationTemplate.name: SS1::Soa::ShapeSearch::ShapeSearch::findShapeSearchProfiles
OperationTemplate.returnDescription: The profiles count, the profiles display value and the default profile is in the structure. The order of the profiles display value is the same as the order of the server setting. The following partial errors may be returned: 117001: Failed to retrieve shape search profiles.

OperationParameter.description: The display value of the profiles in a specific language.
OperationParameter.name: profileLocale

OperationTemplate.description: This operation performs a shape search. The shape search is based on the query string, the shape, the beginning size and the ending size. If the query string is empty, a partial error is returned in Service Data. If the query string is not a Geolus object ID, the result will be empty. Use Cases: The operation provides following user case. Use Case 1: You can perform shape search to get the Teamcenter objects as the search conditions.
OperationTemplate.name: SS1::Soa::ShapeSearch::ShapeSearch::performShapeSearch
OperationTemplate.returnDescription: The list of shape search result which is the object UID and the number of results. The following partial errors may be returned: 117004: The specified Geolus object ID is empty. 117005: Failed to retrieve the shape search result.

OperationParameter.description: The required input parameters including the query string, the shape similarity, the beginning size and the ending size to perform the search.
OperationParameter.name: shapeSearchInput

OperationTemplate.description: This operation checks the status of the Geolus shape search server. This operation should be called before using any other ShapeSearch operation.
OperationTemplate.name: SS1::Soa::ShapeSearch::ShapeSearch::shapeSearchServerQuery
OperationTemplate.returnDescription: An empty response indicates the Geolus server is ready. On failure the following partial error is returned: 117006:Status query failed. The Geolus server is not running.
